For ANY scenario, always answer like:
👉 Step 1: Identify issue
👉 Step 2: Check system (CPU, memory, disk, network)
👉 Step 3: Check logs
👉 Step 4: Fix issue
👉 Step 5: Prevent recurrence




🔥 1. High CPU Issue
❓ Scenario:
Production server CPU is 100%. What will you do?
👉 Answer:
First, I check system load using uptime or top.
Then I identify the process consuming CPU using top or ps aux --sort=-%cpu.
I verify if it’s expected or abnormal.
Then I check logs related to that process.
If required, I restart or kill the process.
Finally, I analyze root cause to prevent recurrence.
💾 2. Disk Full Issue
❓ Scenario:
Server disk is full. Application stopped.
👉 Answer:
I check disk usage using df -h and identify large directories using du -sh *.
If space is not visible, I check for deleted files using lsof | grep deleted.
I clear logs or unnecessary files.
If needed, I extend disk using LVM.
Then I restart the application.
🌐 3. Server Not Reachable
❓ Scenario:
You cannot SSH into server.
👉 Answer:
I check network connectivity using ping.
Then verify IP using ip a.
I check if SSH service is running using systemctl status sshd.
I verify firewall rules.
If still failing, I check logs in /var/log/auth.log.
🌍 4. Website Not Loading
❓ Scenario:
Website is down.
👉 Answer:
I check DNS resolution using nslookup.
Then check server reachability using ping.
I verify if port 80/443 is open using ss -tuln.
Then I check web server status (nginx/apache).
Finally, I review application logs.
🔐 5. Permission Issue
❓ Scenario:
User cannot access a file.
👉 Answer:
I check file permissions using ls -l.
Then verify ownership.
If needed, I update permissions using chmod or chown.
Also check if SELinux is blocking access.
⚙️ 6. Service Not Starting
❓ Scenario:
Service fails to start.
👉 Answer:
I check status using systemctl status.
Then check logs using journalctl -u <service>.
I identify configuration errors or port conflicts.
Fix the issue and restart service.
💾 7. LVM Extension
❓ Scenario:
Need to increase disk space without downtime.
👉 Answer:
I extend logical volume using lvextend.
Then resize filesystem using resize2fs or xfs_growfs.
This can be done without downtime.
📡 8. Network Issue Between Servers
❓ Scenario:
Two servers cannot communicate.
👉 Answer:
I check IP configuration using ip a.
Then test connectivity using ping.
If failed, I check routing using ip route.
I verify firewall rules and security groups.
If needed, I use tcpdump to analyze packets.
🔄 9. Backup Failure
❓ Scenario:
Backup job failed.
👉 Answer:
I check logs of backup tool.
Verify storage availability.
Check permissions on backup directory.
Re-run backup manually and fix issue.
Ensure alerting is configured.
🖥️ 10. VM Performance Issue
❓ Scenario:
VM is slow.
👉 Answer:
I check CPU, memory usage inside VM.
Then check host resource usage (VMware).
Verify if resources are over-allocated.
Check disk I/O performance.
Optimize or increase resources if needed.
🔥 11. DNS Issue
❓ Scenario:
DNS not resolving.
👉 Answer:
I check /etc/resolv.conf.
Test using nslookup.
Verify DNS server reachability.
Restart DNS service if required.
🔐 12. Security Incident
❓ Scenario:
Suspicious login detected.
👉 Answer:
I check logs (/var/log/auth.log).
Identify IP and block using firewall.
Disable compromised user.
Change passwords and enforce policies.
Audit system for further issues.
📊 13. Monitoring Alert
❓ Scenario:
High memory alert from Prometheus.
👉 Answer:
I check memory usage using free -m.
Identify process using top.
Check for memory leaks.
Restart service if needed.
Tune application or increase memory.
⚠️ Golden Pattern (VERY IMPORTANT)
For ANY scenario, follow this structure:
👉 Say this:
“First I verify the issue, then identify root cause using system tools, fix the issue, and finally ensure it doesn’t happen again.”



🔥 1. Load Average High but CPU Low
❓ Scenario:
Load average is high, but CPU usage is low.
👉 Answer:
High load with low CPU usually indicates processes are waiting for I/O.
I check using iostat or top (wa - wait time).
Then I check disk I/O using iotop.
Identify slow disk or heavy read/write process.
Optimize disk or move workload.
💾 2. Disk Space Increasing Automatically
❓ Scenario:
Disk keeps filling up automatically.
👉 Answer:
I check which directory is growing using du.
Then monitor real-time changes using watch du.
Check logs or application generating files.
Implement log rotation or cleanup.
🌐 3. Intermittent Network Issue
❓ Scenario:
Application works sometimes, fails sometimes.
👉 Answer:
I suspect network instability.
I test using continuous ping.
Use tcpdump to analyze packet drops.
Check DNS latency.
Verify load balancer or firewall.
🔐 4. SSH Taking Too Long
❓ Scenario:
SSH login is very slow.
👉 Answer:
Usually due to DNS reverse lookup delay.
I check /etc/ssh/sshd_config and disable UseDNS.
Also check network latency and authentication delays.
⚙️ 5. Service Running but Not Responding
❓ Scenario:
Service is active but not working.
👉 Answer:
I check if port is listening using ss -tuln.
Then test locally using curl localhost.
Check logs for errors.
Verify dependencies (DB, network).
💾 6. Mount Point Not Accessible
❓ Scenario:
NFS mount not working.
👉 Answer:
I check mount using mount command.
Verify NFS server availability.
Check network connectivity.
Check firewall ports (2049).
Remount if needed.
🔄 7. Cron Job Not Running
❓ Scenario:
Scheduled job not executing.
👉 Answer:
I check crontab using crontab -l.
Verify cron service status.
Check logs (/var/log/syslog).
Ensure correct permissions and paths.
🖥️ 8. Server Rebooted Unexpectedly
❓ Scenario:
Server restarted automatically.
👉 Answer:
I check logs using last and journalctl.
Look for kernel panic or OOM issues.
Check hardware or cloud events.
Identify root cause and fix.
📡 9. Port Accessible Locally but Not Remotely
❓ Scenario:
App works on localhost but not from outside.
👉 Answer:
I check firewall rules.
Verify service is listening on correct IP (0.0.0.0).
Check security groups (cloud).
Ensure port is open externally.
🔐 10. Too Many Failed Login Attempts
❓ Scenario:
Multiple failed SSH attempts.
👉 Answer:
I check logs (auth.log).
Block IP using firewall.
Enable fail2ban.
Disable root login.
Use SSH keys.
📊 11. Memory Leak Issue
❓ Scenario:
Memory keeps increasing over time.
👉 Answer:
I monitor memory using top.
Identify process consuming memory.
Check for memory leak in application.
Restart service as temporary fix.
Inform dev team for permanent fix.
🌍 12. DNS Resolution Slow
❓ Scenario:
DNS queries taking too long.
👉 Answer:
I test using dig or nslookup.
Check DNS server response time.
Verify /etc/resolv.conf.
Use faster DNS if needed.
💥 13. System Hanging Frequently
❓ Scenario:
Server becomes unresponsive.
👉 Answer:
I check CPU, memory, disk usage.
Look for high load or I/O wait.
Check logs for errors.
Identify problematic process.
Optimize or restart.
🔄 14. Backup Taking Too Long
❓ Scenario:
Backup job is slow.
👉 Answer:
I check network speed.
Verify disk I/O.
Optimize backup type (incremental).
Schedule during low usage.
🖥️ 15. VMware VM Not Starting
❓ Scenario:
VM fails to start.
👉 Answer:
I check host resources (CPU, RAM).
Verify datastore availability.
Check VM logs.
Fix resource issue or restart host service.

